cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper uses deep learning-based computer vision techniques to analyze 50 million images of street scenes gathered by Google Street View cars to estimate the demographic makeup of the US. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses automated systems to monitor demographic trends, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential of using automated systems to complement labor-intensive approaches, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
